modules.description: Provides functions to capture and redirect standard input and output streams, including reading from and writing to buffers. Works with channel types and byte sequences to manage I/O during test scenarios. Enables precise control over input sources and output destinations in interactive or automated workflows.

Captures output from arbitrary code blocks or file descriptors, returning the collected standard or error output as a string. It supports capturing from specific file descriptors or starting and finishing captures for more controlled output collection. This is useful for testing or logging program output without modifying the original code.
